Month = {{MAR-JUN}},
Abstract = {{This paper examines whether the combined effects of R\&D efforts and the
   types of knowledge obtained from the invention process determine patent
   propensity. With this aim, we investigate a unique, manually collected
   sample of firms and the Spanish and European Patent Offices to analyze
   how the combination of R\&D and knowledge codifiability, observability
   and simplicity influence the patent decision. Our results contribute to
   the literature and assist R\&D managers by showing that codified
